#gigatons
Iron: steel, alloys

#megatons
Aluminium: alloys
Barium: drilling fluid, CRT monitors
Boron: fiberglass, borosilicate glass
Carbon: fossil fuels, plastics, steel, jewelry (diamond)
Chlorine: PVC, disinfection
Chromium: stainless steel, alloys
Copper: electrical wire
Hydrogen: fossil fuel processing, hydrogenation (ammonia, margarine), energy carrier
Lead: ammunition, batteries
Magnesium: alloys, sulfur removal, titanium production
Manganese: steel, alloys
Nickel: stainless steel, alloys
Nitrogen: fertilizer, inert gas, cryogenics
Oxygen: smelting, polyester, oxidizer
Phosphorus: fertilizer
Potassium: fertilizer
Silicon: alloys, semiconductors
Sulfur: sulfuric acid, cellophane (carbon disulfide), vulcanization
Zinc: galvanization, brass
Zirconium: opacifier

#kilotons
Antimony: flame retardant, alloys
Argon: inert gas
Arsenic: alloys, pesticides
Bismuth: lead replacement, compounds
Bromine: flame retardant
Cadmium: batteries
Caesium: drilling fluid, atomic clock
Calcium: steelmaking
Cobalt: alloys, batteries, catalysts
Fluorine: smelting, refrigerants, PTFE, toothpaste
Gold: jewelry, electronics
Helium: cryogenics
Iodine: catalysis, antiseptic
Lithium: batteries
Mercury: thermometers, amalgam
Molybdenium: steel
Niobium: steel
Silver: jewelry, antibiotic
Sodium: preservative
Strontium: CRT monitors
Tin: solder, bronze, alloys
Titanium: pigments, alloys, jewelry, medical implants
Uranium: nuclear power plant fuel, ammunition
Vanadium: steel, ferrovanadium
Wolfram: tungsten carbide, alloys

#tons
Beryllium: radiation windows, gemstones
Gallium: semiconductors (gallium arsenide)
Germanium: optics, semiconductors
Indium: semiconductors
Palladium: catalytic converters
Platinum: catalyst, jewelry
Plutonium: nuclear weapons
Rhenium: superalloys in jet engines
Rhodium: catalytic converters
Ruthenium: electrical contacts, catalysis, jet engines
Tantalum: electronics
Tellurium: alloys, catalysis

Americium: smoke detectors
Deuterium: heavy water in nuclear reactors
Iridium: alloys
Neon: electric signs
Osmium: alloys
Tritium: nuclear weapons
